records.addlTxt:
Defendant Terrence T Lafaive in court, in custody, with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.   Lesli S Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1 and amended Count 5 (repeater struck).  Court finds defendant guilty. Counts 2, 3, 4 and 6 are dismissed and read-in.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 1:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - none) CONSECUTIVE
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy
*Notify treating doctors of cases
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No contact or association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail - balance to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail - balance to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);


COUNT 5:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT STAYED (CREDIT - none) CONSECUTIVE.
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:

*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy
*Notify treating doctors of cases
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No contact or association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (apply cash bail - balance to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail - balance to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);


Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
